title: Upmala Parish
text:
Upmala Parish is an <a href="Administrative%20divisions%20of%20Latvia">administrative unit</a> of <a href="Prei%C4%BCi%20Municipality">Preiļi Municipality</a>, <a href="Latvia">Latvia</a>. From 2009 until 2021, it was part of the former <a href="V%C4%81rkava%20Municipality">Vārkava Municipality</a>
History.
Upmalas <a href="village%20council">village</a> was formed in 1975 from the liquidated part of <a href="Stradi%C5%86i%20village">Stradiņi village</a> and <a href="V%C4%81rkava%20village">Vārkava village</a>. In 1977 part of Upmala village was added to <a href="Ro%C5%BEkalnu%20village">Rožkalnu village</a>. In 1979, part of the <a href="Raunie%C5%A1u%20village">Rauniešu village</a> area was added to Upmalas village. The village was reorganized into a parish in 1990. In 2002, Upmala Parish merged with <a href="Ro%C5%BEkalni%20Parish">Rožkalnu Parish</a> to form <a href="V%C4%81rkava%20Municipality">Vārkava Municipality</a>.
